==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Latin '''video''' "I see", the first-person singular present indicative of '''videre''', meaning "to see".

===Noun===
'''video'''  (''plural:'' '''[[videos]]''')
# [[television]], [[television show]], [[movie]]
# motion picture stored on VHS or some other format
# ''(historically)'' [[VHS]]

: '''Video''' is used in contrast with ''[[audio]]'', which is sound only.

